Adaptive Rendering Engine

Overview

The Adaptive Rendering Engine is a software framework designed to dynamically adjust rendering quality and performance based on system resources, scene complexity, and user requirements. The engine aims to provide optimal visual quality while maintaining stable frame rates.

Features

- Dynamic Level of Detail (LOD)
- Adaptive Resolution Scaling
- Real-time Performance Monitoring
- Resource-Aware Rendering
- GPU and CPU Optimization
- Multi-Platform Support

Objectives

- Improve rendering efficiency.
- Reduce resource consumption.
- Maintain consistent frame rates.
- Enhance user experience.

Technologies

- C++
- OpenGL / Vulkan
- GLSL Shaders
- Python (Testing & Analysis)

